description:
Shell startup is ~860ms. nvm and sdkman are the biggest contributors (~250ms and ~150ms respectively). Replace eager sourcing with lazy-load shims that source the real init script on first invocation of nvm/node/npm/npx (and sdk). Should drop startup well under half a second.

Pattern:
  nvm() { unset -f nvm node npm npx; \. /opt/homebrew/opt/nvm/nvm.sh; nvm "$@"; }
  node() { unset -f nvm node npm npx; \. /opt/homebrew/opt/nvm/nvm.sh; node "$@"; }
  ...
  sdk() { unset -f sdk; source "$SDKMAN_DIR/bin/sdkman-init.sh"; sdk "$@"; }

Also drop the oh-my-zsh `npm` plugin since it eagerly loads npm completions that won't work with lazy nvm anyway.
